    "attributes": {
        "action": "New legislation needed to address 'Bullying in the workplace'",
        "additional_details": "Workplace bullying is repeated, healthharming mistreatment of one or more persons, by one or more perpetrators, in the form of verbal abuse, offensive conduct/behavior and work interference.\r\nIn addition to the emotional and psychological turmoil, victims have their work and career disrupted as well as their personal lives destroyed.",
        "background": "Changes are needed to existing legislation to help eradicate the present high incidences of 'workplace bullying' that are not dealt with appropriately internally & externally causing extreme mental health issues & death - introduction of new legislation, eg resurrection of the Dignity at Work Bill",
